    "where L E is the Eddington luminosity and η is the accretion efficiency (Marconi and Hunt 2003; Graham 2007 Graham, 2016)).",
    "Typical values for these parameters are L/L E ∼ 1/3 and η = 0.1 (Kollmeier et al. 2006; Shen et al. 2008; Edelson et al. 2015).",
    "Although both methods assume the same model, R flux λ,1/2 estimations are a factor of ∼ 2 -3 smaller than R BH λ,1/2 (Collin et al. 2002; Pooley et al. 2007; Morgan et al. 2010) and cannot be reconciled neither through uncertainties in the measured black hole mass, nor, in the case of strongly lensed quasars, through lensing magnification (e.g.",
    "Extended versions of the standard thin-disc model have been formulated (see e.g.",
    "Abramowicz and Fragile 2013; Middleton et al. 2015; Lasota et al. 2015) that include general relativistic corrections, radiative transfer in the disc atmosphere, black hole spin, or disc winds (Novikov and Thorne 1973; Thorne 1974; Hubeny et al. 2000; S ądowski et al. 2011; Davis and Laor 2011)."
